\lim_{x\to0}\frac{\sin(1-\cos(x))}{x^2e^x}
1-\cos(x)
\begin{aligned}L &= \lim_{x \to 0}\frac{\sin(1 - \cos x)}{x^{2}e^{x}}\\ &= \lim_{x \to 0}\frac{\sin(1 - \cos x)}{1 - \cos x}\cdot\frac{1 - \cos x}{x^{2}e^{x}}\\ &= \lim_{x \to 0}\frac{\sin(1 - \cos x)}{1 - \cos x}\cdot\frac{1 - \cos x}{x^{2}}\cdot \frac{1}{e^{x}}\\ &= \lim_{t \to 0}\frac{\sin t}{t}\cdot\lim_{x \to 0}\frac{1 - \cos x}{x^{2}}\cdot \lim_{x \to 0}\frac{1}{e^{x}}\text{ by putting }t = 1 - \cos x \to 0 \text{ as } x \to 0\\ &= 1\cdot\lim_{x \to 0}\frac{1 - \cos x}{x^{2}}\cdot 1\\ &= \lim_{x \to 0}\frac{2\sin^{2}(x/2)}{(x/2)^{2}}\cdot\frac{(x/2)^{2}}{x^{2}}\\ &= 2\cdot 1\cdot\frac{1}{4} = \frac{1}{2}\end{aligned}
